A lesson: The video takes Cheney through a short history of drag saying 'it doesn't take itself too seriously!'

On the show's website, a statement response to Cheney read: 'Y’know we don’t have a clear-cut answer—and maybe there isn’t one. All we know is what a queen told us once: “Drag queens don’t make fun of women, they make fun of society’s expectations of women. If you’re just insulting women that’s not drag—that’s misogyny.”'

However, they did hail Cheney, who is openly gay and married to Heather Poe, with whom she has two children, for another Facebook post recently that championed gay rights.

In it, Cheney slammed her sister Liz for opposing gay marriage, and wrote: 'Liz - this isn't just an issue on which we disagree - you're just wrong - and on the wrong side of history.'

